<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I haven&apos;t read both of them, but I have done research for this reason. I read the Young Adult one because I feel it appealed to me more/ The YA one ha<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I haven't read both of them, but I have done research for this reason. I read the Young Adult one because I feel it appealed to me more/ The YA one has aged down character and has exclusive chapters that have POV's from different characters that we don't get in the adult edition. It also has extra pages to see what beast you are ect. ect. As for the content I believe it is the same though I have not read it so I could not really know. hoped this helped have a wonderful day/<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
