  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2881762583" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2881762583" />
    <a title="mith" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7621359-mith"><img alt="mith" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1644292559p2/7621359.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2881762583?book_show_action=true">Jul 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="mith" class="user" itemprop="url" name="mith" href="/user/show/7621359-mith">mith</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7621359-mith?shelf=2019">2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7621359-mith?shelf=adult">adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7621359-mith?shelf=maaaagic">maaaagic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7621359-mith?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7621359-mith?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7621359-mith?shelf=series">series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7621359-mith?shelf=lgbtq-plus">lgbtq-plus</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7621359-mith?shelf=supernatural-creatures">supernatural-creatures</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7621359-mith?shelf=male-pov">male-pov</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7621359-mith?shelf=royalty">royalty</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2881762583" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17246841356847240040">Thanks to sourcebooks for sending me a copy of this book! I ADORED it!<br/><br/>Kingdom of Exiles was the book I’ve been looking for, for the LONGEST time! I loved playing Pokémon as a child and still love it to pieces now and this has such a great vibe that reminded me of the Pokémon world and it’s games. Have you guys ever played the rescues games on gameboy or the explorers of time/darkness/space for DS? It was like that, with a little bit of the ranger, and of course, the usual regular Pokémon games. </span>
  <span id="freeText17246841356847240040" style="display:none">Thanks to sourcebooks for sending me a copy of this book! I ADORED it!<br /><br />Kingdom of Exiles was the book I’ve been looking for, for the LONGEST time! I loved playing Pokémon as a child and still love it to pieces now and this has such a great vibe that reminded me of the Pokémon world and it’s games. Have you guys ever played the rescues games on gameboy or the explorers of time/darkness/space for DS? It was like that, with a little bit of the ranger, and of course, the usual regular Pokémon games. <br /><br />HOW DOES THAT NOT APPEAL TO YOU? I can’t. I love it so much. <br /><br />This is told from two points of view! You have the charmer Leena and the assassin Noc. Leena is an exiled charmer who had to resort to selling her beasts to stay afloat—a crime that’s punishable by death in her charmer world. And as if THAT isn’t bad enough, someone’s put a hit on her and she’s the target of a dangerous assassin group. Fun times. Guess who has to kill her? I’ll give you one guess. <br /><br />I LOVED LEENA. So much! You can’t help but root for her and her story made me so emo. She has such an amazing personality and I absolutely loved her voice. I loved her arc so much and reading from her point of view was definitely my favourite. <br /><br />I liked Noc but I think I loved his friend group more. I didn’t warm up to everyone but eventually it was easy to get used to their personalities and the camaraderie they share. Noc himself was... okay? I mean he had an interesting character but he was also so hot and so cold. I understood why but WHEW it got sort of tiring eventually. I am extremely curious to see what his past is and learn a bit more about the curse that plagued him during the course of the book. It’s all very shady. <br /><br />I liked the romance! Not my favourite bit, but it’s a double sided sword, as they say. I thought the attraction happened way too early in the beginning, and then later on, their relationship got way deep really fast. Especially for a first book. But that aside, I ended up rooting for them to finally kiss that it just didn’t matter eventually lol. <br /><br />Going off that though, I found the thing at the end a little contradictory? Like the entire book we’re told the most sacred bond a charmer can have is with their beasts. There’s just nothing like it. It’s said MULTIPLE times and I believe it. So when some strange marriage-soul mate thing is introduced at the end, and is said to be EVEN MORE sacred than the beast connection, I just? I found it hard to believe.<br /><br />Overall, what a SOLID start to a new fantasy romance series! I absolutely LOVED the beasts and the bestiary was such an amazing touch. I can’t wait for future books and to read about these characters again. Martineau definitely has a gift with writing and I’m excited to read more from her!</span>
  <a data-text-id="17246841356847240040" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

