<div id="review_2901064130" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2901064130" />
    <a title="Melissasfandomworld" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34871171-melissasfandomworld"><img alt="Melissasfandomworld" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1486125037p2/34871171.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2901064130?book_show_action=true">Jul 23, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melissasfandomworld" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melissasfandomworld" href="/user/show/34871171-melissasfandomworld">Melissasfandomworld</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34871171-melissasfandomworld?shelf=books-owned-english">books-owned-english</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2901064130" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11649411788856942589"><b>
  <blockquote>&quot;𝐿𝑒𝓉 𝓂𝑒 𝓉𝑒𝓁𝓁 𝓎𝑜𝓊 𝓈𝑜𝓂𝑒𝓉𝒽𝒾𝓃𝑔, 𝐿𝑒𝑒𝓃𝒶... <br/>𝒩𝑜 𝓂𝒶𝓉𝓉𝑒𝓇 𝒽𝑜𝓌 𝒽𝒶𝓇𝒹 𝓎𝑜𝓊 𝓉𝓇𝓎, <br/>𝓃𝑜 𝓂𝒶𝓉𝓉𝑒𝓇 𝒽𝑜𝓌 𝓂𝒶𝓃𝓎 𝒷𝒶𝓉𝓉𝓁𝑒𝓈 𝓎𝑜𝓊 𝓌𝒾𝓃, <br/>𝓎𝑜𝓊 𝓌𝒾𝓁𝓁 𝓃𝑒𝓋𝑒𝓇 𝓈𝓊𝓇𝓋𝒾𝓋𝑒 𝓂𝑒.&quot;</blockquote>
</b><br/><br/><b>4,5 beautiful stars</b> to this majestic beast of a book. I don’t think there’s anything better for me than discovering a new favorite within the PNR/fantasy romance genre, so I&apos;m really happy I can add Kingdom of Exiles to my new found favorites and that I just experienced a most wonderful reading experience. I LOVED every single second spend reading this story so insa</span>
  <span id="freeText11649411788856942589" style="display:none"><b>
  <blockquote>"𝐿𝑒𝓉 𝓂𝑒 𝓉𝑒𝓁𝓁 𝓎𝑜𝓊 𝓈𝑜𝓂𝑒𝓉𝒽𝒾𝓃𝑔, 𝐿𝑒𝑒𝓃𝒶... <br />𝒩𝑜 𝓂𝒶𝓉𝓉𝑒𝓇 𝒽𝑜𝓌 𝒽𝒶𝓇𝒹 𝓎𝑜𝓊 𝓉𝓇𝓎, <br />𝓃𝑜 𝓂𝒶𝓉𝓉𝑒𝓇 𝒽𝑜𝓌 𝓂𝒶𝓃𝓎 𝒷𝒶𝓉𝓉𝓁𝑒𝓈 𝓎𝑜𝓊 𝓌𝒾𝓃, <br />𝓎𝑜𝓊 𝓌𝒾𝓁𝓁 𝓃𝑒𝓋𝑒𝓇 𝓈𝓊𝓇𝓋𝒾𝓋𝑒 𝓂𝑒."</blockquote>
</b><br /><br /><b>4,5 beautiful stars</b> to this majestic beast of a book. I don’t think there’s anything better for me than discovering a new favorite within the PNR/fantasy romance genre, so I'm really happy I can add Kingdom of Exiles to my new found favorites and that I just experienced a most wonderful reading experience. I LOVED every single second spend reading this story so insanely much. <br /><br />The world is so immensely interesting with these so called Charmers and their magical beasts and all of the other added fantasy/magical elements like Not and his band of ‘risen from the death’ assassin’s who control darkness and shadows. What a truly wonderful journey this was and I am so sad that I’ll now have to wait until February 2020 before I’m able to read the next installment and return to this world. This is a world I could spend forever in, these characters are ones I want to spent time forever with and the magical writing is one I could keep reading forever. I’m already looking forward to re-read this book when I’ve literally just finished it, so that’s the best sign I could get haha. <br /><br />As a huge PNR fan, I really couldn’t be happier with how this story turned out. This first book in the Charmers series has rapidly made it’s way to my favorites first-book-in-a-PNR-series-list. This was truly such a wonderful start of a new series. I loved the ‘typical’ build up of this story and world building that you come across in a lot of PNR/fantasy romance read, and I specially love how the author then also gave her own twist on it all. I loved getting aquatinted with all these super interesting magical beasts, I loved the sort of quest the characters go on and the forming friendships as well as the forming (slow burn) romance. The set of characters is wonderful and I am so excited to read more about all of them. <br /><br /><b>CONCLUSION</b><br /><br />This book basically has everything present that I could want for in a PNR, so I couldn’t be happier about that. The only reason I didn’t give it an entire 5 star rating is because it was mostly always predictable to me. I don’t mind that though, because a lot of books (no matter which genre) are predictable. And as long as the depth and development of a story as well as the characters and writing is so well executed as in this book, I don’t mind it one bit but I can’t give it a full 5 star rating. But really; I’m so excited and happy that this book turned out to be one I fell in love with. I was so excited to read this one and when I’m That excited, I’m also always a little afraid of the book not living up to its expectations, you know? Thankfully, this one did live up to it’s expectations. I really can’t wait to see what more this author has in store for us. I am hooked to her writing, I am hooked to the magical world she’s created and the set of amazing characters that had me falling in love hard. I want MORE MORE MORE! <br /><br /><b>Highly Recommended - Must Read</b><br />This is one I’d definitely recommend, as you might’ve guessed haha, to anyone who loves a good PNR! A perfect book to pick for fans of Amanda Bouchet’s Kingmaker Chronicles or Gena Showalter’s Lords of the Underworld for example. Still need to know more about why I fell in love? Here’s my checklist:<br /><br />- <b>Uniquely Magical Beasts</b> that you want all for yourself &gt; CHECK<br />- <b>A group of sexy ‘risen from the death’ Assassin’s</b> who have your heart doing funny things in your chest and leave you a drooling fangirl mess &gt; CHECK<br />- <b>A truly wonderful and intense slow burn romance</b> that’s so beautifully developed &gt; CHECK<br />- <b>(Dark) Magical elements</b> present like the super awesome dark magic the Assassin’s possess to name one. Or the amazing abilities the Beast’s possess &gt; CHECK<br />- A good amount of <b>Action &amp; Adventure</b> that had me flipping the pages so fast I couldn’t stop reading the book until I was finished, well after midnight &gt; CHECK <br /><br />I’m truly sad I am finished reading this book, because I don’t want to depart with this world. I wish the author was already done writing this series, so I could’ve binge read them all back to back hihi. Fan-freaking-tastic is what this book is! Over and out.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11649411788856942589" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


